{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1496968365,"nonce":"m2sTD1/m7T2ReBVAjHpGXJGwzfo=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyMzQ2OTE4ODU=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1354","origin":"github"},"title":"SnpEff Download issues, originally v4.1.0 and still in v4.3k.0","message":"The tool only makes the first genome from a nested .zip available in UI \n\n**Tool:** SnpEff Download Download a new database (Galaxy Version 4.1.0)\n\n**Repo:** https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repository?repository_id=93a5efea7e957b53\u0026changeset_revision=7adfd0589f49\n\n**Repo tool version:** 4.3k.0\n\n_Is an update at http://usegalaxy.org the solution or is the problem still in the newer version of the tool as well or is there some configuration problem?_ \n\nping @bgruening @davebx @natefoo \n\n---\n**Version 4.1.0 issue**\n\nThe requested genome is in the list of the available genomes and the stderr for the database download tool _indicates that all of the data is downloaded_. However, only the first genome in the .zip bundle is available through the UI. \n\nZip archives are not parsed through upload in a default Galaxy (nor at Galaxy Main). Only the first file is loaded. Not sure if related but seemed worth mentioning.\n\nhttps://usegalaxy.org/u/jen/h/snpeff-database-download-test-history\n\n\u003cimg width=\"970\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-06-08 at 4 40 58 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8999735/26955562-5aca7866-4c6c-11e7-92e2-c7e7cf682bf1.png\"\u003e\n\n**Genome requested by the tool:**\n\nhttps://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/genome/?term=txid264462[Organism:noexp]\n**Bdellovibrio_bacteriovorus_HD100_uid61595**\nrefseq: NC_005363.1\nINSDC: BX842601.2\n\n**Genome accessible by SnpEff tool:**\n\nhttps://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/genome/486?genome_assembly_id=167053\n**Bacillus_thuringiensis_BMB171_uid49135**\nchr refseq: NC_014171.1\t\nchr INSDC: CP001903.1\nplsm refseq: NC_014172.1\nplsm INSDC: CP001904.1\n\nExamining the target .zip when obtained directly (using the same path that the tool uses) shows that the zip does have the target genome in the set. The genome available through the UI is the first in the archive.\n\n\u003e $ curl https://managedway.dl.sourceforge.net/project/snpeff/databases/v4_1/snpEff_v4_1_NCBI_bacterial_4.zip \u003e snpEff_v4_1_NCBI_bacterial_4.zip\n\u003e   % Total    % Received % Xferd  Average Speed   Time    Time     Time  Current\n\u003e                                  Dload  Upload   Total   Spent    Left  Speed\n\u003e 100  102M  100  102M    0     0  5530k      0  0:00:18  0:00:18 --:--:-- 5725k\n\u003e $ unzip snpEff_v4_1_NCBI_bacterial_4.zip\n\u003e Archive:  snpEff_v4_1_NCBI_bacterial_4.zip\n\u003e   inflating: wsu/home/eq/eq83/eq8302/snpEff/data/Bacillus_thuringiensis_BMB171_uid49135/snpEffectPredictor.bin  \n\u003e   inflating: wsu/home/eq/eq83/eq8302/snpEff/data/Bacillus_thuringiensis_Bt407_uid177931/snpEffectPredictor.bin\n\u003e   inflating: wsu/home/eq/eq83/eq8302/snpEff/data/Bacillus_thuringiensis_HD_771_uid173374/snpEffectPredictor.bin\n\u003e etc.. for all \n\n\u003e $ ls\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_BMB171_uid49135\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_Bt407_uid177931\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_HD_771_uid173374\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_HD_789_uid173860\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_MC28_uid176369\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_YBT_1518_uid229419\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_serovar_IS5056_uid190186\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_serovar_chinensis_CT_43_uid158151\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_serovar_finitimus_YBT_020_uid158875\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_serovar_konkukian_97_27_uid58089\n\u003e Bacillus_thuringiensis_serovar_kurstaki_HD73_uid189188\n\u003e Bacillus_toyonensis_BCT_7112_uid227218\n\u003e Bacillus_weihenstephanensis_KBAB4_uid58315\n\u003e Bacteriovorax_marinus_SJ_uid82341\n\u003e Bacteroides_CF50_uid222805\n\u003e Bacteroides_fragilis_638R_uid84217\n\u003e Bact